\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {9}{\ignorespaces \textbf  {Theoretical Framework: When O/R Index Applies.} O/R Index predicts success in discovery tasks with dense rewards (green, $|r| = 0.70$). Effect weakens in execution tasks where behavioral variance converges, and in sparse reward settings ($|r| = 0.35$). Lower O/R correlates with higher success in all applicable regimes. Examples: discovery = exploration environments; execution = fixed-target navigation.}}{19}{figure.9}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:framework}{{9}{19}{\textbf {Theoretical Framework: When O/R Index Applies.} O/R Index predicts success in discovery tasks with dense rewards (green, $|r| = 0.70$). Effect weakens in execution tasks where behavioral variance converges, and in sparse reward settings ($|r| = 0.35$). Lower O/R correlates with higher success in all applicable regimes. Examples: discovery = exploration environments; execution = fixed-target navigation}{figure.9}{}}
